one.english: It is yet another common day in this dull, drab world in which I specifically enlighten it and bless it with my presence. Nary a moment goes by in which every living creature must yield to my whim for I am beauty incarnate.

two.english: What demonic trickery is this in which the sun itself denies me its warm and supple light. I require to bask in such holy warmth which cannot be given by earthly domains.

three.english: Lo and foth, foul creature. Thy mortal coil is but seconds if you proceed to unsuccessfully entertain me, for thine skin too soft by tooth and claw.

four.english: You curse me, you do. Curse me to an existence where I must endure such banes as hunger, one for which your irresponsibility has brought failure to cause.

five.english: I am quite pleased due to my local surroundings, though I am quick to boredom. You may continue to entertain me but know it is in vain.

six.english: DO NOT DISTURB UPON PAIN OF DEATH

seven.english: Beware, mine prey, for you shall meet your nimrod as he approacheth...

eight.english: You have failed me, pitiful blob of flesh and breath. The bowels of my being wretch in absolute suffering caused from a complete diet of insolence.

nine.english: You daft creature! You dare spoil the the earthly grounds for which upon I lay with your presence?! This will be an act of aggression I none shall forgive.

ten.english: Unfounded tall wooden barricade, I demand you depart and allow me to transition outside!
